\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. A. septentrionalis} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 142 (1753). Annual, somewhat pubescent below with simple, forked and stellate hairs. Leaves 9-35 × 3-10 mm, oblong-lanceolate or elliptical, dentate, sessile or very shortly petiolate. Scapes 8-30 cm, 1-several. Inflorescence 5- to 30-flowered; involucral bracts 2-4 mm, oblong or lanceolate. Pedicels at least 3 times as long as bracts. Calyx 2·5-3·5 mm, divided to about the middle. Corolla 4-5(-6) mm, white or pink. Seeds 0·5-1 mm, numerous.{\i  Dry places. N. & C. Europe, extending southwards to the S.W. Alps and S. Russia.} Au Cz Da Fe Ga Ge He It No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, W, E) Su.
