\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. A. filiformis} Retz., {\i Obs. Bot.}{\b  2}: 10 (1781). Annual, glabrous below. Leaves 25-40 × 3-7 mm; lamina ovate to elliptical,dentate, distinctly petiolate. Scapes 10-15 cm, usually several, glabrous or sparsely glandular-pubescent above. Inflorescence many-flowered, lax; involucral bracts 1·5-3 mm, lanceolate. Pedicels 15-50 mm, at least 10 times as long as bracts, glandular-pubescent. Calyx 1·5-2·5 mm, glabrous. Corolla 2-3 mm, white. Seeds c. 0·5 mm, numerous.{\i  Damp places. U.S.S.R., northwards from} c. 53°{\i  N}. Rs (N, B, C, W, E).
