\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. A. obtusifolia} All.,{\i  Fl. Pedem. }{\b 1}: 90 (1785). Perennial, laxly caespitose or rosettes solitary. Leaves 6-20 × 1·5-4 mm, lanceolate or oblong-lanceolate, tapered to the base, scarcely petiolate, more or less sparsely hairy and ciliate. Scapes 1-several, 2-12 cm, more or less densely tomentose with stellate or forked hairs. Inflorescence 1- to 7-flowered; involucral bracts 2-3·5 mm, linear-lanceolate, puberulent. Pedicels 1-4(-7) times as long as bracts, densely hairy with stellate hairs. Calyx 3-4 mm, densely pubescent. Corolla 6-9 mm in diameter, white or pink. 2n = 36, 38.{\i  Rocks and screes; calcifuge. • Mountains of C. Europe, extending southwards to the S.W. Alps and N. Appennini; mountains of Balkan peninsula southwards to Macedonia.} Au Bu Cz Ga Ge He It Ju Po Rm.
