\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. A. carnea} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 142 (1753). Perennial, laxly caespitose. Leaves 4-20(-35) × 1-2 mm, linear, sometimes fleshy and keeled, pubescent or glabrous on the surfaces, ciliate. Scapes 1-4, 1-6 cm, more or less densely pubescent with stellate or forked hairs. Inflorescence 2- to many-flowered; involucral bracts 2-5 mm, linear-lanceolate, ciliate or glabrous. Pedicels 1-2 times as long as bracts, densely hairy with stellate hairs. Calyx 2·5-6 mm, sparsely hairy. Corolla 5-8 mm, white or pink.{\i  Rocks and screes; calcifuge. • Mountains of W. Europe from the C. Pyrenees to the Vosges and eastwards to} 8° 10' {\i E. in the W.C. Alps.} Ga He Hs Tt.
